post.body: Working at Max Muscle in San Clemente for Louise..
I stayed at the Wyland Waikiki, it was really nice!!
Relaxing after a LOng week of training myself and others! Spending the weekend in Laguna Beach!
Lots of surfing at Doheny today- early this morning and the afternoon... Water is perfect- no wetsuit needed! Going again in the a.m...
checking emails; getting ready to go visit Grandpa; then coming home for a sunset run on the beach. I love San Clemente!
Between clients- trying to get stuff done! Where does the time go? Why do I never have anything done?! Too much to do, so little time! :)
At home- trying to get chores done so that I can enjoy most of the weekend! Oceanfest this week in beautiful San Clemente! Love this town!
Added some comparison pic's of the other ladies that I competeted against in bikini- tall category. www.lizfitness.com
just posted some of the professional pics from the competition... www.lizfitness.com
http://tinyurl.com/6mnv8z Picture's from the fitness competition! More to come- it was a blast!
My neighbors are having a party- gotta go do more cardio and then eat more protein. No party for Lizzie. Competition in 5 days- stay strong!
One week out from Fitness Competition. I feel overtrained and tired but so exited about next weekend- I hope all of this work pays off!
Cleaning my messy apartment; washing veggies, getting ready to go do first set of cardio at the gym, too hot to do it outside. Stairs later.
Two weeks until Fitness Competition, Feeling irritable, tired, hungry, and sick of dieting and cardio. I need to snap out of it. Bahumbug.
I watched an episode of Workout this morning- where they go to boot camp for the weekend- such drama! I can't stop watching....
3 weeks out; dropped 2 lbs. in a week and down to 14% bodyfat; feeling good, but pretty depleted by the time I get to my 2nd bout of cardio
down to 2-1-0 starch rotation and double cardio sessions; Need to write programs now so that my clients don't suffer from my lack of carbs!
eating a salad,I also needing to find a Mom's day gift, but the tea basket won't work.. She doesn't drink tea.... any other ideas?
Enjoying this great day is BEAUTIFUL San Clemente!!!
Rode my bike to stairs, did 40 minutes of them, rode my bike for another 10; Now enjoying spinach salad with chicken and onions and Galeos
